	)
	(text "COM connectors follow the \nTI EVM 4-pin format for \nhigh-side and low-side \ndaisy-chain interfaces.\n\nEach connector carries one \ndifferential COM pair only; \nunused pins are left NC."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 191.008 146.558 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "689954c5-f6a4-4276-a040-55841478b4ca")
	)
	(text "Power\nTest\nPoints"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 364.744 102.362 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "9d4ab40a-89db-4424-b86e-fa6fb11b6580")
	)
	(text "TO ECU\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 358.14 136.144 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "cda0ba5b-4ef2-45ba-adcc-9c9e941e4537")
	)
	(text "BMU TOP-LEVEL ARCHITECTURE\n\nThis page summarizes the BMU interface board, including power distribution,\nSTM32 control, BQ79600 battery-monitor communication, CAN-FD interface,\nshunt-board interface, external connectors, and debug/test access points.\n\n1. POWER\nJ3 receives the 12 V BMU input. BMU-POWER provides fuse protection, power switch,\nPMOS input protection, 12 V to 5 V conversion, 5 V to 3.3 V regulation, and\npower-status LEDs.\n\n2. BQ79600 / COM BRIDGE\nBMU-COM Bridge connects the STM32 to the external battery-monitor daisy-chain /\nring network through the BQ79600 host bridge. J1 and J2 follow the TI EVM-style\n4-pin COM connector format; unused pins are intentionally left NC.\n\n3. MCU / DEBUG\nBMU-MCU contains the STM32 controller, reset circuit, STDC14 SWD connector,\nBQ79600 UART interface, CAN control signals, shunt-board interface, reserved GPIO,\nand shutdown signal.\n\n4. CAN-FD\nBMU-CAN provides the MCP2562FD CAN-FD physical-layer interface to the vehicle ECU /\nCAN network. J12 carries CANH, CANL, and CAN_GND. Termination is populated only\nwhen the BMU is an end node.\n\n5. SHUNT / GPIO / SAFETY\nThe shunt interface provides I2C, 3.3 V, ground, and ALERT_SHUNT. Reserved GPIO\nsignals and SHUTDOWN are kept for future expansion and shutdown/safety integration.\n\nRecommended test points:\n+12V, VIN_PROTECTED, +5V, +3V3, GND, UART1_TX, UART1_RX,\nBQ_FAULT_N, CAN_TX, CAN_RX, CAN_STBY, CANH, CANL, I2C_SCL, I2C_SDA,\nALERT_SHUNT, SHUTDOWN.\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 34.036 144.018 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 2.032 2.032)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "d92171e3-4207-439c-8e4d-3e2560cdbd94")
	)
	(text "TO SHUNT"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 381 181.61 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "e48130a6-b692-4aba-b776-4c5e8e817183")
	)
	(text "12V → 5V → 3.3V"
